              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* Less than 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 0 feet, *Reach (Long):* 0 feet.  Multiple Tiny creatures can occupy the same square.  At least four can fit in a single square, though the GM might determine that even more can fit.  Tiny creatures can occupy a space larger creature as well, and if their reach is 0 feet, they must do so in order to attack.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 331,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "4abdb1bc8002ecad825f0a1a3e55ac58",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Clockwork",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 364",
                "aonid": 276,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 364",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core 2",
              "page": 364,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Clockworks are intricate, complex constructs that can be programmed to perform specific functions. A clockwork creature must be wound regularly to function.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 35,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
